# Sotiro Portfolio Website

A personal portfolio website built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## Overview

This project is a black-and-white themed personal portfolio website designed to showcase who I am, the projects I have worked on, my career ambitions, and ways to contact me.

The website features a clean one-page scrolling layout with a bold landing section, fade-in content sections, project showcases, and contact links.

## Features

- Bold centered landing page
- Black and white minimalist design
- Smooth scrolling navigation
- About Me section
- Projects section
- Career Goals section
- Contact section
- Resume / external links support
- Fade-in scroll effects

## Technologies Used

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

## Project Structure

    portfolio-website/
    ├── index.html
    ├── style.css
    └── script.js

## Sections Included

### Home
The landing section introduces the portfolio with the title **SOTIRO** and the subtitle **Explore Sotiro**.

### About Me
A section that introduces who I am, my background, and my interests in software engineering.

### Projects
A showcase of projects I have worked on, including short descriptions and live demo links.

### Career Goals
A section outlining my ambitions, professional direction, and goals after university.

### Contact
A section with ways to connect with me, including email, LinkedIn, resume, and other external links.

## How to Run the Website

1. Download or clone the repository
2. Open the project folder in Visual Studio Code
3. Open `index.html` in a browser

Optional:
- Use the **Live Server** extension in VS Code for easier development

